The paper deals with unsupervised representation learning for images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of different self-supervised feature learning methods, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches upon the type of information captured by shallow layers in deep networks, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses deep learning techniques, which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the visualization of learned representations, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
